<subSubSection id="4AB7D3D1FF84FFBFFF65FBF3FA8CFB7E" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0212805AFF84FFBFFF65FBF3FA8CFB7E" blockId="21.[136,1452,337,1229]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF84FFBFFF65FBF3FEFEFB88" bold="true" box="[189,318,1057,1083]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF84FFBFFDD4FBF1FD63FB8F" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Raddi" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[524,675,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estrellensis">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF84FFBFFDD4FBF1FD63FB8F" box="[524,675,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">T. estrellensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. This species is distinguished mainly by branches slightly to sharply winged, leaves with a bullate adaxial surface and the manybranched trichomes at the base, and foveolate abaxial surface. 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF84FFBFFC8FFBB8FB9BFB37" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Raddi" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[855,1115,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estrellensis">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF84FFBFFC8FFBB8FB9BFB37" box="[855,1115,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Tibouchina estrellensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF84FFBFFAC4FBB9FA6CFB37" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Desrousseaux" baseAuthorityYear="1797" box="[1308,1452,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF84FFBFFAC4FBB9FA6CFB37" box="[1308,1452,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">T. granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which differs by the flat leaves on both surfaces and the presence of basal 1–2-branched strigose trichomes on the adaxial surface. Additional illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF84FFBFFDBCFB60FCE5FB7E" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[612,805,1202,1229]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" pagination="288 - 418" refId="ref24137" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1885) Tibouchina (Melastomaceae). In: Martius, C. F. P., Eichler, A. G. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis 14 (3): 288 - 418." type="journal article" year="1885">Cogniaux (1885)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF84FFBFFCE9FB60FC3EFB7F" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F." box="[817,1022,1202,1228]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" refId="ref24954" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F. (1997) Estudos taxonomicos de Tibouchina sect. Pleroma (D. Don) Cogn. (Melastomataceae). Tese de Doutorado. Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Campinas, 191 pp." type="book" year="1997">Guimarães (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF84FFBFFBE1FB60FA88FB7E" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A." box="[1081,1352,1202,1229]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" pagination="591 - 646" refId="ref22935" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Souza, M. L. D. R., Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A. (2006) Melastomataceae na Reserva Biologica de Poco das Antas, Silva Jardim, Rio de Janeiro, Brasil: aspectos floristicos e taxonomicos. Rodriguesia 57 (3): 591 - 646." type="journal article" year="2006">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF84FFBFFB63FB61FB33FB7F" box="[1211,1267,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
